This paper is about click-through rate (CTR) prediction in online advertising, which is a common problem in machine learning and data mining. The proposed method involves pruning redundant parameters in a deep factorization machine, which is a type of neural network used for modeling feature interactions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques, which are also common in machine learning. The use of deep learning models and feature engineering also suggests that the paper could belong to the Data Structures (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves image processing techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category.
